WEBVTT

1
00:02:06.150 --> 00:02:08.150
you can find me on  and pless support me
https://www.youtube.com/@titoGamersHaven

2
00:02:08.170 --> 00:02:10.050
Another crossing burned.

3
00:02:10.130 --> 00:02:11.630
We might never reach Tumbleton.

4
00:02:12.590 --> 00:02:15.010
So how long will it take you
to build the bloody thing again?

5
00:02:16.470 --> 00:02:18.310
We will have to find another crossing.

6
00:02:18.390 --> 00:02:20.970
-take the long way round.
-The queen will abhor this delay.

7
00:02:22.560 --> 00:02:24.600
Lord Piper. take 100
of your fastest riders

8
00:02:24.690 --> 00:02:26.060
and make for Stoney Sept.

9
00:02:26.150 --> 00:02:27.610
Secure the barge and transit there.

10
00:02:29.400 --> 00:02:31.900
That puts us back by a week.
but we can do no better.

11
00:02:31.990 --> 00:02:35.530
It's our last chance to ford the river
with an army of this size.

12
00:02:45.040 --> 00:02:47.080
Will we continue to suffer this Cole

13
00:02:47.170 --> 00:02:49.590
and his band of hangers-on?

14
00:02:49.670 --> 00:02:52.710
They flit about us
like fucking deer flies.

15
00:02:52.800 --> 00:02:55.760
another thing that
we do not endure in the North.

16
00:02:55.840 --> 00:02:57.550
Better deer flies than frostbite.

17
00:02:58.760 --> 00:03:02.720
But Criston Cole I am past enduring.
North or South.

18
00:03:02.810 --> 00:03:08.400
Then loose my wolves and me on the hunt.
and we will bring him down.

19
00:03:09.820 --> 00:03:11.400
Or we could play at his game.

20
00:03:48.190 --> 00:03:49.310
Ambush!

21
00:03:54.940 --> 00:03:56.490
We're under attack!

22
00:04:00.740 --> 00:04:02.120
To the next crossing. then?

23
00:04:02.200 --> 00:04:05.700
They'll make for Stoney Sept
and we'll once more be ahead of them.

24
00:04:05.790 --> 00:04:07.160
Fall back!

25
00:04:44.280 --> 00:04:46.370
If I'd have known
we were expecting guests.

26
00:04:46.450 --> 00:04:48.120
I would have made up the beds.

27
00:04:48.210 --> 00:04:49.750
We're looking for Aemond Targaryen.

28
00:04:49.830 --> 00:04:52.210
-the Kinslayer.
-Ah. yes. There's been a horde of you

29
00:04:52.290 --> 00:04:55.960
since the ungrateful queen
announced her bounty.

30
00:04:56.800 --> 00:04:59.340
Well. you won't find your quarry here.

31
00:04:59.420 --> 00:05:04.140
There's an old man who churns the butter.
but he's blind in both eyes.

32
00:05:05.180 --> 00:05:07.220
And the boy who feeds the horses.

33
00:05:08.270 --> 00:05:10.690
And then there are the ghosts.

34
00:05:10.770 --> 00:05:14.060
Seems you have not learned
the history of this place

35
00:05:14.150 --> 00:05:16.190
and the laborers who built it...

36
00:05:18.030 --> 00:05:20.860
who died here in chains...

37
00:05:21.820 --> 00:05:23.410
in service to Harren the Cruel.

38
00:05:28.580 --> 00:05:30.160
This castle breathes.

39
00:05:35.630 --> 00:05:39.210
She swallows the greedy. the heedless.

40
00:05:42.510 --> 00:05:45.970
Her founding stones were watered
with the blood of men.

41
00:05:48.010 --> 00:05:49.980
And she's always thirsty.

42
00:06:08.580 --> 00:06:10.080
Oi! You bloody craven?!

43
00:06:12.330 --> 00:06:13.830
Fuck this place.

44
00:06:29.220 --> 00:06:30.680
Can you hear me?

45
00:06:32.770 --> 00:06:34.390
Stay back! Stay back!

46
00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:39.020
My brother. Aegon. he was here.

47
00:06:39.110 --> 00:06:40.860
His face was on fire.

48
00:06:41.740 --> 00:06:46.160
I saw him. He was clutching at me.
dragging me down into the dark.

49
00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:49.160
-My brother.
-It's just the dream again. That's all.

50
00:06:54.580 --> 00:06:56.880
It's just the dream again.

51
00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:07.050
She saw it.

52
00:07:08.090 --> 00:07:12.020
She said I would die.
that I ruined everything.

53
00:07:12.100 --> 00:07:13.310
No.

54
00:07:23.110 --> 00:07:24.820
Mother.

55
00:07:55.520 --> 00:07:57.690
None may enter.
save at our queen's direction.

56
00:07:57.770 --> 00:08:00.940
It is a matter of some delicacy.

57
00:08:02.570 --> 00:08:06.110
I'm not certain how familiar you are
with disorders of the...

58
00:08:07.200 --> 00:08:09.530
female persuasion.

59
00:08:09.610 --> 00:08:10.700
Hm?

60
00:08:24.300 --> 00:08:28.050
I must thank you again
for your loyalty. Grand Maester.

61
00:08:28.130 --> 00:08:30.180
I flatter myself to think
that I have ever been

62
00:08:30.260 --> 00:08:32.140
a faithful servant to Your Grace.

63
00:08:33.180 --> 00:08:35.390
More than that. you've been a friend.

64
00:08:37.600 --> 00:08:39.230
But we have now a new queen.

65
00:08:41.150 --> 00:08:44.860
And I find myself under some scrutiny.

66
00:08:44.940 --> 00:08:50.070
I fear I can no longer offer you
assistance after today

67
00:08:50.160 --> 00:08:52.370
without making the proper disclosures.

68
00:08:54.330 --> 00:08:55.490
I understand.

69
00:09:10.180 --> 00:09:11.680
I don't want it.

70
00:09:12.800 --> 00:09:13.890
You must.

71
00:09:14.930 --> 00:09:17.220
It could be a boy. Do you see?

72
00:09:17.310 --> 00:09:19.180
Aegon's heir. a rival to Joffrey.

73
00:09:20.140 --> 00:09:21.690
To Rhaenyra herself.

74
00:09:26.860 --> 00:09:29.070
She will kill it. She will have no choice.

75
00:09:30.570 --> 00:09:32.110
Or if she does not.
she will take it from you.

76
00:09:32.200 --> 00:09:34.530
Aemond still lives. as far as we know.

77
00:09:34.620 --> 00:09:35.830
He's at Harrenhal.

78
00:09:35.910 --> 00:09:37.580
No. he was there. but he has fled.

79
00:09:37.660 --> 00:09:39.830
-He's vanished.
-I have seen him.

80
00:09:41.120 --> 00:09:44.250
He burns. but without fire.

81
00:09:50.380 --> 00:09:55.100
If Aemond threatens Rhaenyra's rule.
she will use the child as her shield.

82
00:09:56.510 --> 00:09:58.810
I can't do it.

83
00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:00.730
Helaena. please. Please.

84
00:10:01.850 --> 00:10:03.810
For your own sake.
do you not wish to be free?

85
00:10:04.810 --> 00:10:06.060
I can't.

86
00:10:07.570 --> 00:10:10.030
-No. No.
-Think of it. think of it as a cup of tea.

87
00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:11.650
Nothing more.

88
00:10:11.740 --> 00:10:13.320
But it isn't.

89
00:10:13.400 --> 00:10:16.950
No. No. it's not. Listen to me.
Listen to me. it is a blessing.

90
00:10:17.030 --> 00:10:19.950
It is a remedy taught
to the masters of the Citadel.

91
00:10:20.950 --> 00:10:23.500
It has delivered me
from disgrace and ruin.

92
00:10:23.580 --> 00:10:26.000
It has delivered Rhaenyra herself
when she was young.

93
00:10:26.080 --> 00:10:27.670
And it will deliver you. too.

94
00:10:29.590 --> 00:10:30.920
-Helaena. Please. please.
-No.

95
00:10:31.010 --> 00:10:32.970
Listen to me.

96
00:10:33.050 --> 00:10:34.720
Will you bear a child

97
00:10:34.800 --> 00:10:38.010
who will be never more
than a hostage or a pawn?

98
00:10:38.100 --> 00:10:39.260
It's mine!

99
00:10:40.390 --> 00:10:42.350
It's my own. it's mine!

100
00:10:48.730 --> 00:10:50.780
I had hoped a seat on the council
would suffice

101
00:10:50.860 --> 00:10:52.860
as recompense for House Frey's loyalty.

102
00:10:52.940 --> 00:10:57.200
But Harrenhal was to be our recompense.
payment for giving your Winter Wolves

103
00:10:57.280 --> 00:10:59.990
passage across the Twins.
promised by your own son.

104
00:11:00.080 --> 00:11:02.410
-My son is dead.
-And now. I discover

105
00:11:02.500 --> 00:11:05.120
that you have pledged
our castle as a trophy.

106
00:11:05.210 --> 00:11:07.330
free to any hedge knight
who can bring you the head

107
00:11:07.420 --> 00:11:09.920
-of Aemond Targaryen.
-You. yourself. are welcome to try.

108
00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:12.590
Cregan Stark's army
has crossed the Trident.

109
00:11:12.670 --> 00:11:15.840
and we expect the crown's
word to be honored.

110
00:11:15.930 --> 00:11:18.550
no matter if some grubby sellsword

111
00:11:18.640 --> 00:11:21.390
has dubbed himself Lord of Harrenhal
in the meanwhile.

112
00:11:26.640 --> 00:11:28.310
For now. however.

113
00:11:28.400 --> 00:11:31.070
I would be pleased
to join Your Grace's council.

114
00:11:37.240 --> 00:11:39.700
What could anyone possibly
want in Wendish Town?

115
00:11:39.780 --> 00:11:44.200
Not Wendish Town itself. Your Grace.
but a small village at the outskirts.

116
00:11:44.290 --> 00:11:45.910
There were several farms burned.

117
00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:48.500
and the men we talked to were
certain it was Vhagar herself.

118
00:11:48.580 --> 00:11:50.960
The Sea Snake's bastard.
now a dragonrider.

119
00:11:51.040 --> 00:11:52.840
-That's his brother.
-Lord Darry is our ally.

120
00:11:52.920 --> 00:11:55.170
Aemond may be provoking us.

121
00:11:55.260 --> 00:11:57.510
By sacking a farm or three? To what end?

122
00:11:57.590 --> 00:11:59.010
Dragons need to eat.

123
00:11:59.090 --> 00:12:00.600
The White Worm. she was called.

124
00:12:00.680 --> 00:12:03.010
But they are fugitives.
We will root them out soon enough.

125
00:12:03.100 --> 00:12:05.100
-The whore.
-Mm-hmm.

126
00:12:10.230 --> 00:12:12.570
There was a skirmish last night
at the Dragon Gate.

127
00:12:12.650 --> 00:12:14.190
Horses were required to dispel it.

128
00:12:14.280 --> 00:12:15.740
If only the Lady Mysaria had been there

129
00:12:15.820 --> 00:12:17.780
with her promised bread
and ladlefuls of stew.

130
00:12:17.860 --> 00:12:20.570
Or if. by some miracle.
the king consort's City Watch

131
00:12:20.660 --> 00:12:24.700
had shown a penny's worth of restraint
pursuing the pettiest of crimes.

132
00:12:24.790 --> 00:12:27.370
-the pettiest of criminals--
-Did anyone see where Vhagar flew?

133
00:12:27.460 --> 00:12:29.210
We went with all speed
to take up the trail.

134
00:12:29.290 --> 00:12:30.670
but it was two days cold.

135
00:12:30.750 --> 00:12:32.540
Once again. Aemond is nowhere to be found.

136
00:12:32.630 --> 00:12:36.300
Two of our gold cloaks were found dead
in the street this morning.

137
00:12:36.380 --> 00:12:38.420
Put to the blade by an unknown hand.

138
00:12:38.510 --> 00:12:39.590
Where was this?

139
00:12:39.680 --> 00:12:41.930
-Flea Bottom.
-Flea Bottom.

140
00:12:42.010 --> 00:12:43.970
Mm. has ever been a realm unto itself.

141
00:12:44.060 --> 00:12:47.850
Quite ungovernable. full of undesirables.

142
00:12:47.930 --> 00:12:51.150
Vhagar appears while Ormund Hightower

143
00:12:51.230 --> 00:12:53.230
gathers himself at Tumbleton
to some hidden purpose.

144
00:12:53.310 --> 00:12:55.360
We need not waste our sweat
fretting over a fox

145
00:12:55.440 --> 00:12:57.110
gone to ground.
If you will not burn him...

146
00:12:57.190 --> 00:12:58.610
-He is not a f--
-...then my army

147
00:12:58.700 --> 00:13:00.030
will root him out soon enough.

148
00:13:00.110 --> 00:13:01.950
As to that. there is fresh news

149
00:13:02.030 --> 00:13:04.200
from Lord Tully's camp.

150
00:13:04.280 --> 00:13:06.160
Their march has been slowed
by interference

151
00:13:06.240 --> 00:13:08.370
from Ser Criston Cole and his men.

152
00:13:08.450 --> 00:13:11.620
River crossings are being burned
before the army can reach them.

153
00:13:11.710 --> 00:13:13.250
Go back to the Riverlands.

154
00:13:13.330 --> 00:13:15.380
If Aemond has shown himself once.
he may do so again.

155
00:13:15.460 --> 00:13:18.170
Take no risk. but ascertain his path.
his purpose.

156
00:13:18.260 --> 00:13:19.630
If I may. Your Grace.

157
00:13:19.720 --> 00:13:22.760
We arrived back only this morning.

158
00:13:22.840 --> 00:13:25.010
The Lady Baela has not eaten.
much less slept.

159
00:13:25.100 --> 00:13:26.850
I am more than ready to fly.

160
00:13:26.930 --> 00:13:28.470
It will not serve us
if your eyes are weary

161
00:13:28.560 --> 00:13:30.390
and your beast fatigued.

162
00:13:30.480 --> 00:13:31.940
I will send Daemon.

163
00:13:33.190 --> 00:13:36.480
I will go once I have dealt
with this business in the city.

164
00:13:36.570 --> 00:13:38.740
Our fallen soldiers.
An accounting must be made.

165
00:13:38.820 --> 00:13:41.200
-Do you not agree?
-I am able. Your Grace.

166
00:13:41.280 --> 00:13:42.910
The loss to our City Watch

167
00:13:42.990 --> 00:13:45.780
is a crime. to be sure.
but Ser Luthor will investigate.

168
00:13:46.660 --> 00:13:49.200
-It is not a matter for the crown.
-They are my men.

169
00:13:49.290 --> 00:13:52.000
And we depend on those men now
to secure your rule.

170
00:13:54.290 --> 00:13:56.540
Especially since their wages
have been withheld.

171
00:14:00.050 --> 00:14:01.550
-Your Grace.
-Not now.

172
00:14:02.930 --> 00:14:04.340
Is it always like this?

173
00:14:05.140 --> 00:14:06.640
Mm.

174
00:14:06.720 --> 00:14:07.970
Daemon.

175
00:14:10.350 --> 00:14:12.440
Have I somehow found myself
back on Dragonstone?

176
00:14:12.520 --> 00:14:14.900
That my voice must again
compete with yours?

177
00:14:14.980 --> 00:14:17.110
On the contrary. I have pledged
to fulfill your command.

178
00:14:17.190 --> 00:14:18.020
Just...

179
00:14:18.110 --> 00:14:18.940
later.

180
00:14:19.030 --> 00:14:21.280
I'm in no mood to jest.
What does it make of me

181
00:14:21.360 --> 00:14:23.610
if you will obey me only at a time
and place of your own choosing?

182
00:14:23.700 --> 00:14:25.370
You are the queen.

183
00:14:25.450 --> 00:14:27.240
I act in your interest.

184
00:14:27.330 --> 00:14:30.040
Good. My interest is Vhagar.

185
00:14:30.120 --> 00:14:31.620
Mine too. But we have time enough.

186
00:14:31.700 --> 00:14:34.790
Aemond is afraid.
He has fled once already before you.

187
00:14:34.870 --> 00:14:37.710
-We are in no danger.
-There is treachery somewhere.

188
00:14:37.790 --> 00:14:39.420
and I seek to uncover it.

189
00:14:39.500 --> 00:14:41.760
What you seek is revenge.

190
00:14:41.840 --> 00:14:45.220
And gods know I do not grudge you that.
but revenge may wait.

191
00:14:45.300 --> 00:14:47.510
At this moment. there is
a disturbance in your city.

192
00:14:47.600 --> 00:14:49.810
and you. yourself. are its likely cause.

193
00:14:52.270 --> 00:14:54.640
I did not ask Ser Luthor to be brutal.

194
00:14:54.730 --> 00:14:57.360
You need not have
asked him anything at all.

195
00:14:57.440 --> 00:14:59.820
Will you let yourself
be rattled by vapid taunts.

196
00:14:59.900 --> 00:15:01.650
by the painting of stripes
on tavern walls?

197
00:15:01.730 --> 00:15:04.700
They are more than taunts.
They are an insult to my sons.

198
00:15:04.780 --> 00:15:06.700
A challenge to my very legitimacy.

199
00:15:06.780 --> 00:15:08.620
You are the Queen of Dragons.

200
00:15:08.700 --> 00:15:10.740
Your strength is your legitimacy.

201
00:15:10.830 --> 00:15:12.080
Your Grace?

202
00:15:18.670 --> 00:15:20.040
Glad news.

203
00:15:20.710 --> 00:15:23.550
Young Prince Joffrey
has returned this hour from the Vale.

204
00:15:26.470 --> 00:15:28.720
I'm told he's asked for you.

205
00:15:30.390 --> 00:15:34.810
I will come to him when I'm able.
I'm sure he's tired.

206
00:15:40.480 --> 00:15:42.110
It is long past the nightingale.

207
00:15:42.190 --> 00:15:44.030
I don't care.

208
00:15:44.110 --> 00:15:45.570
Which way is West?

209
00:15:46.530 --> 00:15:47.660
I have no idea.

210
00:15:52.660 --> 00:15:55.620
-If I may say. Your Grace--
-I'm not going back.

211
00:15:55.710 --> 00:15:58.330
-We have nowhere else to go.
-You heard what I did.

212
00:15:58.420 --> 00:16:00.460
Vhagar has been sighted at Wendish Town.

213
00:16:00.540 --> 00:16:02.500
Two days ago.
Who knows where she may be now?

214
00:16:02.590 --> 00:16:05.130
Well. Harrenhal. then.
Someone there will know something.

215
00:16:05.210 --> 00:16:07.470
Look. Aemond must have left
a message or a sign.

216
00:16:07.550 --> 00:16:09.640
-We can pick up his trail.
-It's 100 leagues

217
00:16:09.720 --> 00:16:11.180
to Harrenhal. Your Grace. and the fields

218
00:16:11.260 --> 00:16:13.510
and woods are teeming with Rivermen.

219
00:16:13.600 --> 00:16:16.390
This is more than a folly.
It is dangerous.

220
00:16:16.480 --> 00:16:19.480
Fucking seven fucking hells!

221
00:16:21.150 --> 00:16:23.690
What would you do if you found him. hm?

222
00:16:23.770 --> 00:16:27.530
Your brother is a coiled viper.
and you are...

223
00:16:27.610 --> 00:16:31.570
you are hungry. and broken.
and spent. and we are alone.

224
00:16:31.660 --> 00:16:32.990
If we were to be discovered--

225
00:16:33.080 --> 00:16:35.240
Stop telling me what I can't do!

226
00:16:38.580 --> 00:16:40.000
This is his fault.

227
00:16:41.210 --> 00:16:42.210
Everything.

228
00:16:43.290 --> 00:16:48.170
Every one of my miseries is of his making.
and I swear before the Warrior himself.

229
00:16:48.260 --> 00:16:52.720
I'm going to find him and fucking kill him
or die in the attempt.

230
00:16:53.930 --> 00:16:54.930
Hm.

231
00:17:18.500 --> 00:17:20.000
You know me. I think.

232
00:17:22.290 --> 00:17:23.420
By reputation.

233
00:17:23.500 --> 00:17:28.590
It is my privilege now to listen
to the whispers of the Red Keep.

234
00:17:28.670 --> 00:17:30.970
-The guests you receive...
-What is it that you want?

235
00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:33.840
...and the gifts they bring.

236
00:17:35.760 --> 00:17:37.220
Show it to me.

237
00:17:53.320 --> 00:17:55.030
My daughter has been unwell.

238
00:17:55.120 --> 00:17:57.450
As you see. she suffers
terrible headaches.

239
00:17:57.540 --> 00:18:01.000
The maester is kind enough to tend to her.

240
00:18:01.080 --> 00:18:03.330
And yet the flask is full.

241
00:18:08.630 --> 00:18:10.840
I took a lover after Viserys.

242
00:18:11.840 --> 00:18:15.430
The queen herself knows the truth of it.
I was careless. to my shame.

243
00:18:19.390 --> 00:18:21.930
It's a difficult thing.
but I should no longer delay.

244
00:18:33.990 --> 00:18:37.070
Was he a lord or a commoner?

245
00:18:37.160 --> 00:18:38.990
Or perhaps both?

246
00:18:41.910 --> 00:18:44.500
I must appeal to you. Lady Mysaria.

247
00:18:46.250 --> 00:18:48.420
You of all people must understand the...

248
00:18:49.550 --> 00:18:52.420
the indignities we women endure.

249
00:18:54.470 --> 00:18:56.590
There is surely no need for this
to be spoken of again.

250
00:18:56.680 --> 00:18:59.640
You would not. of course.
seek to deceive the queen.

251
00:19:02.270 --> 00:19:04.140
I am her prisoner.

252
00:19:06.270 --> 00:19:08.190
As you were once. if I'm not mistaken.

253
00:19:14.990 --> 00:19:16.740
As you say.

254
00:19:23.540 --> 00:19:24.910
Have you ever seen the Hightower

255
00:19:25.000 --> 00:19:26.460
at Oldtown. Ser Criston?

256
00:19:27.420 --> 00:19:28.630
I've heard tell of it.

257
00:19:29.790 --> 00:19:31.800
Ormund and I had a game.

258
00:19:32.590 --> 00:19:33.920
to "run the tower."

259
00:19:35.220 --> 00:19:37.090
You'd start at the base before dawn

260
00:19:37.180 --> 00:19:39.430
and aim to be the first one
to see the sun rise

261
00:19:39.510 --> 00:19:41.010
from the beacon.

262
00:19:41.100 --> 00:19:42.930
Of course. I let him win.

263
00:19:43.970 --> 00:19:45.770
He was a thin-skinned twat even then.

264
00:19:46.770 --> 00:19:48.600
Mm.

265
00:19:48.690 --> 00:19:53.980
At that moment. when the sun rises
over the Seven Kingdoms.

266
00:19:54.070 --> 00:19:55.990
hundreds and hundreds of miles...

267
00:19:57.700 --> 00:19:59.990
I hope to show it to you one day.

268
00:20:01.700 --> 00:20:03.870
You could make a home
at Oldtown. Ser Criston.

269
00:20:03.950 --> 00:20:06.750
A knight of your stature
would be most welcome...

270
00:20:08.540 --> 00:20:10.170
to serve our house there.

271
00:20:16.670 --> 00:20:18.590
Halt! Stay back!

272
00:20:23.890 --> 00:20:25.600
Stay clear!

273
00:20:28.440 --> 00:20:29.770
Hold your ground!

274
00:20:31.150 --> 00:20:32.520
Stand your ground!

275
00:20:42.410 --> 00:20:44.580
Crow's feet.

276
00:20:45.790 --> 00:20:46.950
Gods.

277
00:20:47.040 --> 00:20:48.790
Are they ahead of us?

278
00:21:40.550 --> 00:21:43.180
Your hand was heavier
than warranted by the crime.

279
00:21:43.260 --> 00:21:46.350
I was well schooled
in those manners. was I not?

280
00:21:46.430 --> 00:21:48.100
I had the finest of captains.

281
00:21:49.640 --> 00:21:52.390
In any case. the queen wanted it stopped.

282
00:21:52.480 --> 00:21:55.020
The queen's son is dead.
She must be excused her impulses.

283
00:21:55.110 --> 00:21:58.150
-Oh. you'd have me refuse her?
-No. rather temper her.

284
00:21:58.230 --> 00:21:59.150
Tend to her humors.

285
00:21:59.240 --> 00:22:01.780
Not every whim needs to be
pursued with equal vigor.

286
00:22:01.860 --> 00:22:04.620
You know. they cut their bowels
as well as their throat.

287
00:22:04.700 --> 00:22:06.200
Did they tell you that?

288
00:22:06.280 --> 00:22:09.410
Good men dying in agony in their own shit.

289
00:22:10.410 --> 00:22:11.960
We will pay the villains back in kind.

290
00:22:12.040 --> 00:22:13.870
What is the mood among the men?

291
00:22:13.960 --> 00:22:15.840
They complain about their wages.
or lack of them.

292
00:22:15.920 --> 00:22:17.340
I shall address them.

293
00:22:17.420 --> 00:22:19.840
A rousing speech from
the Rogue Prince himself.

294
00:22:19.920 --> 00:22:22.130
I'm not sure that's gonna make up
for a steady wage anymore.

295
00:22:22.220 --> 00:22:24.050
If I lead them. they will follow.

296
00:22:24.130 --> 00:22:26.100
It's been a minute

297
00:22:26.180 --> 00:22:28.390
since you were the Prince of Flea Bottom.

298
00:22:28.470 --> 00:22:31.770
Most of the men were in
swaddling clothes when you--

299
00:23:32.700 --> 00:23:34.040
What is our standing?

300
00:23:34.120 --> 00:23:36.370
Battlements are being raised
with haste. my lord.

301
00:23:36.460 --> 00:23:40.840
But we lack in timber. and men. and time.

302
00:23:40.920 --> 00:23:42.960
Then levy more conscripts.

303
00:23:43.050 --> 00:23:45.590
and fell every tree
from here to Bitterbridge.

304
00:23:45.670 --> 00:23:47.220
We must secure our walls.

305
00:23:47.300 --> 00:23:48.930
Rhaenyra's host is surely on the march.

306
00:23:50.300 --> 00:23:53.430
The maester tells me you've been
most assiduous in your lessons.

307
00:23:55.310 --> 00:23:57.440
We are making a study on my forebears

308
00:23:57.520 --> 00:23:59.230
on the Hightower side.

309
00:23:59.310 --> 00:24:02.820
I mean. their battles. their enemies.

310
00:24:02.900 --> 00:24:04.860
It has been three days
now spent in the pursuit

311
00:24:04.940 --> 00:24:06.320
of these dry histories.

312
00:24:09.780 --> 00:24:11.330
Dry. did you say?

313
00:24:13.790 --> 00:24:15.540
No. Of course not.

314
00:24:18.420 --> 00:24:21.170
Or rather. they may
seem dry at first glance.

315
00:24:21.250 --> 00:24:22.800
but to learn fr...

316
00:24:24.090 --> 00:24:28.760
To venerate our ancestors.
that is a noble task.

317
00:24:28.840 --> 00:24:30.470
And I'm grateful for it.

318
00:24:31.720 --> 00:24:33.260
Good.

319
00:24:33.350 --> 00:24:35.520
It would please me to hear you recite.

320
00:24:39.690 --> 00:24:42.110
We have parsed out the conflicts

321
00:24:42.190 --> 00:24:46.780
between House Greyjoy and Houses Peake

322
00:24:46.860 --> 00:24:48.860
and Osgrey and Gardener.

323
00:24:48.950 --> 00:24:50.070
House Dayne of Dorne--

324
00:24:50.160 --> 00:24:51.700
And Meria Martell?

325
00:24:53.490 --> 00:24:55.490
The Yellow Toad of Dorne.

326
00:24:58.830 --> 00:25:00.670
I should have a word with your tutor.

327
00:25:02.290 --> 00:25:04.550
She was the only woman ever
to have been gifted

328
00:25:04.630 --> 00:25:07.010
with a truly military mind.

329
00:25:09.170 --> 00:25:12.260
Though the gods divested her
of beauty in turn.

330
00:25:13.100 --> 00:25:14.600
A blind princess.

331
00:25:14.680 --> 00:25:17.770
Hideous. hairless. thick of waist.

332
00:25:19.390 --> 00:25:21.730
She does not sound so formidable.

333
00:25:24.310 --> 00:25:26.280
When Aegon the Conqueror
claimed her lands.

334
00:25:26.360 --> 00:25:27.690
she refused to submit.

335
00:25:29.030 --> 00:25:30.900
She declared him a usurper.

336
00:25:30.990 --> 00:25:32.450
And all those that marched for him.

337
00:25:32.530 --> 00:25:33.990
traitors to the Seven Kingdoms.

338
00:25:35.370 --> 00:25:40.370
And she swore that Dorne
would ever be unbowed. unbent.

339
00:25:47.050 --> 00:25:50.130
A great host descended
from the Red Mountains.

340
00:25:50.220 --> 00:25:52.510
we Hightowers regrettably among them.

341
00:25:52.590 --> 00:25:54.430
Meria poisoned her own wells.

342
00:25:54.510 --> 00:25:57.260
hid her soldiers
in the very sand of the desert.

343
00:25:58.390 --> 00:26:00.390
Her castle. when they found it. was empty.

344
00:26:00.480 --> 00:26:02.940
They thought that she was vanquished.

345
00:26:03.020 --> 00:26:07.070
But she rose up out of the darkness
and slaughtered them in their beds.

346
00:26:09.280 --> 00:26:12.400
Is she a hero. then? Or a villain?

347
00:26:19.290 --> 00:26:22.790
The Targaryens knew
nothing of our civilization.

348
00:26:22.870 --> 00:26:24.370
the Faith. the Citadel.

349
00:26:24.460 --> 00:26:26.210
What they had.

350
00:26:26.290 --> 00:26:29.760
what they still have. is strength.

351
00:26:31.090 --> 00:26:33.430
Their armies.
the obscenity of their dragons.

352
00:26:34.260 --> 00:26:36.850
Meria Martell outwitted her enemy.

353
00:26:37.810 --> 00:26:41.980
A cunning mind can resist
the most savage of beasts.

354
00:26:43.390 --> 00:26:46.940
And Dorne remains unbroken even today.

355
00:27:04.830 --> 00:27:06.000
I was lucky.

356
00:27:08.210 --> 00:27:09.460
Let us start again.

357
00:27:32.320 --> 00:27:34.740
Never apologize for victory.

358
00:27:43.910 --> 00:27:45.500
I have had these made.

359
00:27:56.090 --> 00:27:57.470
Do you think it a good likeness?

360
00:28:00.140 --> 00:28:03.970
You are the sign our allies
have been waiting for.

361
00:28:04.060 --> 00:28:07.940
The son of Viserys.
the beacon shining from the High Tower.

362
00:28:09.310 --> 00:28:13.070
From the lowliest of the faithful
to Borros Baratheon himself.

363
00:28:19.910 --> 00:28:22.330
Oh. No. you can't touch that.

364
00:28:23.580 --> 00:28:24.790
Helaena?

365
00:28:27.120 --> 00:28:28.290
Do you know why?

366
00:28:29.290 --> 00:28:33.130
They eat the leaves of the nightshade.
but that would be death for you or me.

367
00:28:33.210 --> 00:28:34.420
It's a puzzle.

368
00:28:34.500 --> 00:28:35.920
Jaehaera. come with me.

369
00:28:41.640 --> 00:28:42.930
Come.

370
00:28:47.640 --> 00:28:49.810
Listen now. dearest. We must leave here.

371
00:28:49.900 --> 00:28:51.360
This very evening.

372
00:28:52.980 --> 00:28:54.690
There seems to be
some trouble in the city.

373
00:28:54.780 --> 00:28:58.070
and some of Rhaenyra's soldiers
must go to help the City Watch.

374
00:28:58.150 --> 00:28:59.950
We will have one guard tonight
instead of two.

375
00:29:03.950 --> 00:29:05.240
Your necklace.

376
00:29:05.330 --> 00:29:07.370
I tendered it to a maid. She will help us.

377
00:29:08.580 --> 00:29:11.330
There is a hidden door that
leads out in Aemond's chamber.

378
00:29:12.250 --> 00:29:13.790
Below the keep and beyond its walls.

379
00:29:14.710 --> 00:29:17.050
The one the men used
when they came to kill my boy?

380
00:29:19.170 --> 00:29:20.590
The room is Baela's now.

381
00:29:21.840 --> 00:29:23.600
And she will no doubt be out hunting.

382
00:29:25.560 --> 00:29:26.770
With luck. we may escape

383
00:29:26.850 --> 00:29:29.060
and melt into the streets
of King's Landing.

384
00:29:29.140 --> 00:29:30.730
And Jaehaera?

385
00:29:32.350 --> 00:29:33.940
Her room is guarded.

386
00:29:34.820 --> 00:29:37.690
If she were to cry out. even once...

387
00:29:38.940 --> 00:29:40.950
-then that would be the end.
-I will not leave her.

388
00:29:42.660 --> 00:29:45.700
The road ahead will not be safe for her.

389
00:29:45.780 --> 00:29:50.580
Here. she has nursemaids to care for her.
and Rhaenyra will not harm her.

390
00:29:50.660 --> 00:29:52.670
Her rivals would never
raise a girl up to rule. and...

391
00:29:53.960 --> 00:29:55.590
and it might be prudent.

392
00:29:55.670 --> 00:29:58.210
in fact. for the queen
to take the child to ward.

393
00:29:58.300 --> 00:30:01.680
We may even be able to--
to send for her one day.

394
00:30:08.890 --> 00:30:10.640
You look away when you lie.

395
00:30:15.440 --> 00:30:19.230
It has been days since Vhagar was here.
She feeds. then eludes us.

396
00:30:20.400 --> 00:30:23.410
We have traversed the Trident
50 times in the last fortnight.

397
00:30:24.660 --> 00:30:26.660
For now. we must rest.

398
00:30:26.740 --> 00:30:29.700
Could Aemond be crossing
into the Westerlands to hide?

399
00:30:29.790 --> 00:30:31.540
The Lannisters are allies.

400
00:30:31.620 --> 00:30:33.670
and there are caves and crannies
aplenty in those mountains.

401
00:30:33.750 --> 00:30:35.580
And I'll be pleased
to explore them with you

402
00:30:35.670 --> 00:30:37.710
when you've had a sleep and a meal.

403
00:30:37.790 --> 00:30:39.300
-He may be moving by night--
-Baela!

404
00:30:42.720 --> 00:30:44.760
-My lady.
-It is well enough for you.

405
00:30:44.840 --> 00:30:48.310
The queen sees you as her talisman.
a sign from the gods. but I--

406
00:30:48.390 --> 00:30:49.680
It wasn't your fault.

407
00:30:49.770 --> 00:30:51.560
She won't look at me.

408
00:30:53.270 --> 00:30:54.900
And I cannot say I blame her.

409
00:30:57.060 --> 00:30:59.190
The truth is. Addam. I wanted to go.

410
00:30:59.270 --> 00:31:01.030
I saw myself a hero.

411
00:31:02.400 --> 00:31:04.990
Turning the tide of a great battle and...

412
00:31:06.320 --> 00:31:07.950
proving my worth to the realm.

413
00:31:08.030 --> 00:31:10.830
I have the same desire. as do others.

414
00:31:10.910 --> 00:31:13.250
It is pride. and I am punished for it.

415
00:31:15.040 --> 00:31:16.540
My future was ordained.

416
00:31:17.830 --> 00:31:19.250
I was one day to be queen.

417
00:31:20.170 --> 00:31:22.550
My path lay straight before me. and now--

418
00:31:22.630 --> 00:31:24.300
Your path has vanished.

419
00:31:24.380 --> 00:31:26.130
Though it has been replaced. perhaps.

420
00:31:27.760 --> 00:31:29.100
By an adventure.

421
00:31:29.180 --> 00:31:31.810
I'll be married off. likely enough.

422
00:31:31.890 --> 00:31:35.600
to some ancient.
self-regarding lord in Pyke.

423
00:31:35.690 --> 00:31:37.440
with enough hoarded gold
to pay Rhaenyra's debts.

424
00:31:37.520 --> 00:31:39.360
And then. I'll come and find you.

425
00:31:40.360 --> 00:31:41.730
And we'll fly to exile.

426
00:31:43.860 --> 00:31:45.450
But only if we eat first.

427
00:31:51.990 --> 00:31:53.410
Vhagar!

428
00:31:55.160 --> 00:31:56.420
She's gone.

429
00:31:58.460 --> 00:31:59.790
No.

430
00:31:59.880 --> 00:32:02.590
No. no. she will not abandon me.

431
00:32:02.670 --> 00:32:06.630
I know only that she flew in the night
and I did not see where.

432
00:32:07.720 --> 00:32:09.300
Maybe she was afraid.

433
00:32:15.350 --> 00:32:16.940
Am I a prisoner?

434
00:32:49.220 --> 00:32:50.590
No.

435
00:32:55.560 --> 00:32:57.480
Without her. I'm nothing.

436
00:32:58.640 --> 00:33:01.270
-You are mistaken.
-I must find her.

437
00:33:02.810 --> 00:33:06.230
And how will you do that
if the dragon has fled?

438
00:33:08.110 --> 00:33:09.820
The queen hunts her as well.

439
00:33:12.910 --> 00:33:14.490
The queen?

440
00:33:14.580 --> 00:33:16.870
I told you. King's Landing has fallen.

441
00:33:18.370 --> 00:33:20.500
I thought I dreamed it.

442
00:33:25.380 --> 00:33:26.510
Aegon?

443
00:33:27.380 --> 00:33:29.340
The queen says he's dead.

444
00:33:30.470 --> 00:33:31.720
And that you killed him.

445
00:33:36.180 --> 00:33:38.600
Though I do not know
how much of that to believe.

446
00:33:40.890 --> 00:33:44.400
He is dead because he will not let me be.

447
00:33:49.690 --> 00:33:50.950
He...

448
00:33:51.780 --> 00:33:53.240
he tormented me.

449
00:33:56.410 --> 00:33:57.910
My childhood...

450
00:33:58.830 --> 00:34:00.210
I worshiped him.

451
00:34:09.130 --> 00:34:10.760
And yet our mother...

452
00:34:13.840 --> 00:34:15.140
Sometimes...

453
00:34:16.470 --> 00:34:18.350
the child that grieves her...

454
00:34:19.810 --> 00:34:21.850
is the one a mother loves best.

455
00:34:23.100 --> 00:34:24.100
Hm?

456
00:34:27.980 --> 00:34:29.320
Who are you?

457
00:34:32.030 --> 00:34:33.860
One that has been grieved.

458
00:34:42.250 --> 00:34:43.370
Go on.

459
00:34:44.290 --> 00:34:45.290
Say it.

460
00:34:48.420 --> 00:34:49.840
My dragon is dead.

461
00:34:50.800 --> 00:34:52.220
I'm a pathetic cripple.

462
00:34:53.220 --> 00:34:57.680
And there is no possible scenario
in which I make it to Wendish Town

463
00:34:57.760 --> 00:34:59.680
to kill my stupid fucking brother.

464
00:34:59.760 --> 00:35:03.230
Now as you should say. should we--
should we return to the camp. Your Grace?

465
00:35:04.850 --> 00:35:07.690
I do not care to be
discovered here unguarded.

466
00:35:07.770 --> 00:35:09.110
and less so when darkness falls.

467
00:35:09.190 --> 00:35:13.240
He was Cole's little pet. do you remember?
A prodigy with the sword.

468
00:35:14.110 --> 00:35:16.450
Father withdrew me from
the tournaments. of course.

469
00:35:17.240 --> 00:35:20.620
Can't even remember the pretext anymore.

470
00:35:20.700 --> 00:35:23.290
Probably just afraid
that I'd fall off my horse.

471
00:35:23.370 --> 00:35:26.330
So. I had to sit and applaud him.

472
00:35:26.420 --> 00:35:28.250
Aemond the champion.

473
00:35:30.210 --> 00:35:32.130
And such a quick student.

474
00:35:32.210 --> 00:35:34.590
Fucking fluent in High Valyrian.

475
00:35:42.390 --> 00:35:46.310
I'm sure he thought I was a terrible king.
but what I could have been if I was...

476
00:35:47.060 --> 00:35:49.480
...given his fucking advantages.

477
00:35:49.560 --> 00:35:52.360
And Mother indulged him.
She loved him more. is the truth of it.

478
00:35:52.440 --> 00:35:55.740
Poor darling Aemond
and his scabby little eye.

479
00:35:55.820 --> 00:35:58.660
And now he's killed me.
and the whole fucking realm knows it.

480
00:36:05.460 --> 00:36:07.920
-I must say. Your Grace.
-What?

481
00:36:08.000 --> 00:36:10.420
All this time we've been together...

482
00:36:12.750 --> 00:36:14.840
from the moment you were injured. in fact.

483
00:36:14.920 --> 00:36:17.760
flying drunk into a battle
to which you were not invited...

484
00:36:18.680 --> 00:36:22.310
you've done nothing but whinge

485
00:36:23.430 --> 00:36:28.310
and self-flagellate with a tenacity
I find astonishing.

486
00:36:28.400 --> 00:36:32.020
You. who had every advantage in life.

487
00:36:32.110 --> 00:36:36.070
You. who had every chance to shine.

488
00:36:36.150 --> 00:36:41.530
Firstborn son. prince of the realm.
the finest tutors. the finest knights

489
00:36:41.620 --> 00:36:43.240
instructing you in the sword.

490
00:36:44.200 --> 00:36:47.210
A dragon so beautiful.
they named him after the sun itself.

491
00:36:49.920 --> 00:36:52.750
You could have risen to greatness.

492
00:36:53.670 --> 00:36:58.170
But instead. you trampled
your birthright in the mud.

493
00:37:00.930 --> 00:37:02.220
You lazed...

494
00:37:03.430 --> 00:37:05.770
reveling in mediocrity...

495
00:37:06.930 --> 00:37:09.140
fucking anything in sight
and drinking yourself

496
00:37:09.230 --> 00:37:11.900
into oblivion with
your sycophantic friends.

497
00:37:16.320 --> 00:37:17.820
I will tell you the truth.

498
00:37:19.280 --> 00:37:20.860
You were a terrible king.

499
00:37:22.620 --> 00:37:23.950
But worse than that...

500
00:37:25.030 --> 00:37:28.710
you are a terrible man.

501
00:37:44.510 --> 00:37:45.640
Don't.

502
00:37:47.640 --> 00:37:49.180
They said you were here.

503
00:37:49.850 --> 00:37:51.270
I thought there was some mistake.

504
00:37:51.350 --> 00:37:57.070
They require of me. perhaps.
just some show of deference. or regard.

505
00:37:57.150 --> 00:37:59.110
-The people or the Seven?
-Both.

506
00:38:00.490 --> 00:38:02.990
There can be no harm in it. at the least.
You could try it.

507
00:38:17.420 --> 00:38:19.760
Four of my men lie dead.

508
00:38:19.840 --> 00:38:21.380
Six. if you count the two from yesterday.

509
00:38:21.470 --> 00:38:23.800
All gold cloaks.
all killed in the same way.

510
00:38:24.680 --> 00:38:25.850
Throats cut.

511
00:40:44.780 --> 00:40:46.190
You are tired.

512
00:40:50.070 --> 00:40:51.780
You hear the wind in these vaulted towers

513
00:40:51.870 --> 00:40:53.990
and imagine their omens
when there are none.

514
00:40:56.830 --> 00:40:58.620
Hm? These are men only.

515
00:40:59.670 --> 00:41:01.750
-Nothing more.
-Then why can't you find them?

516
00:41:30.360 --> 00:41:32.240
You are more than this.

517
00:41:36.580 --> 00:41:38.450
This costs us precious time.

518
00:41:38.540 --> 00:41:39.830
That is no doubt their goal.

519
00:41:39.910 --> 00:41:43.580
They knew we would leave the road
when we abandoned our mounts.

520
00:41:43.670 --> 00:41:46.750
This land may be theirs. but even
they could not cause thorns

521
00:41:46.840 --> 00:41:50.340
and brambles to spring
from the earth in our path.

522
00:41:50.430 --> 00:41:51.930
And men are talking of desertion.

523
00:41:52.010 --> 00:41:54.720
Ser Criston. Friend.

524
00:41:56.470 --> 00:41:59.310
They see no sense in continuing
with this plan and to speak truth.

525
00:41:59.390 --> 00:42:01.230
nor do I. We grow weak.

526
00:42:01.310 --> 00:42:03.600
-Stoney Sept still lies far ahead.
-Mm.

527
00:42:09.320 --> 00:42:10.950
If we leave the track here...

528
00:42:11.860 --> 00:42:13.530
cut straight through the lowlands
toward the crossing.

529
00:42:13.610 --> 00:42:15.530
we may yet still gain a day or two
over Tully's host.

530
00:42:52.530 --> 00:42:54.360
Just hire the fucking ship.

531
00:43:02.160 --> 00:43:03.790
What ship might that be?

532
00:43:05.790 --> 00:43:07.290
Seven hells.

533
00:43:16.220 --> 00:43:17.800
He's gone. My lady. be quick.

534
00:43:30.780 --> 00:43:33.780
You said the nurse
would meet us with Jaehaera.

535
00:43:33.860 --> 00:43:35.150
And so she will. at the other end.

536
00:43:35.240 --> 00:43:37.070
-Where?
-Come. now. Quickly.

537
00:43:46.920 --> 00:43:49.290
Did you imagine I wouldn't be watching?

538
00:43:52.090 --> 00:43:54.800
So it is she who is with child.

539
00:43:54.880 --> 00:43:56.630
An inconvenient heir.

540
00:43:56.720 --> 00:43:59.100
There is no need for Rhaenyra to hear
of what transpired tonight.

541
00:43:59.180 --> 00:44:02.060
I will keep no more secrets
from the queen.

542
00:44:02.140 --> 00:44:04.270
And what will be the result
if you tell her?

543
00:44:05.600 --> 00:44:07.400
We are already at her mercy.

544
00:44:08.560 --> 00:44:10.860
In but a short time. Helaena's condition
will make itself known.

545
00:44:10.940 --> 00:44:12.980
as these things cannot help but do.

546
00:44:13.070 --> 00:44:14.820
It is not for me to decide.

547
00:44:17.200 --> 00:44:19.160
I heard tell of the White Worm.

548
00:44:21.080 --> 00:44:21.950
Years ago.

549
00:44:22.740 --> 00:44:26.210
She dealt in secrets and extortion.
and I knew men who feared her.

550
00:44:28.250 --> 00:44:31.670
She had the cunning to play all sides.
not just lapdog to the queen.

551
00:44:31.750 --> 00:44:34.920
These are rich words
in the mouth of a Hightower.

552
00:44:35.010 --> 00:44:38.550
I simply urge you to think of yourself.

553
00:44:39.890 --> 00:44:42.100
There is good in Rhaenyra. but...

554
00:44:43.140 --> 00:44:45.020
the crown is a weight that crushes.

555
00:44:49.850 --> 00:44:51.650
Rhaenyra will do in the end
what she has to do.

556
00:44:51.730 --> 00:44:53.820
and what she has to do will be dire.

557
00:44:55.440 --> 00:44:57.450
There is only one who can walk
that path with her.

558
00:44:57.530 --> 00:44:58.820
and she chose him long ago.

559
00:44:58.910 --> 00:45:00.530
She knows what Daemon is.

560
00:45:00.620 --> 00:45:03.160
They have ever been two sides of a coin...

561
00:45:03.240 --> 00:45:04.740
as much as she may deny it.

562
00:45:07.660 --> 00:45:10.420
Her attentions may be on you now.

563
00:45:10.500 --> 00:45:14.250
that you bathe in the warm light
of her gaze. but...

564
00:45:15.800 --> 00:45:19.130
will you stake so high a wager
on the whims of a dragonrider?

565
00:45:20.220 --> 00:45:21.550
I want to go out.

566
00:45:23.600 --> 00:45:25.220
-Not now. dearest.
-Yes.

567
00:45:27.810 --> 00:45:29.310
I need to see the moon.

568
00:45:29.390 --> 00:45:31.150
The window will have to do.

569
00:45:32.610 --> 00:45:36.110
Speak. and you serve no one.
you gain the queen no advantage.

570
00:45:36.190 --> 00:45:39.450
But if you say nothing. no harm is done.

571
00:45:40.490 --> 00:45:42.620
You earn yourself favor
with the Hightowers...

572
00:45:45.620 --> 00:45:47.750
if a time should come
when you have need of it.

573
00:46:15.190 --> 00:46:17.360
He tried to stay awake
for you. Your Grace.

574
00:46:22.450 --> 00:46:25.030
Come on. keep moving!

575
00:46:25.120 --> 00:46:26.990
Keep moving now!

576
00:46:51.600 --> 00:46:53.270
Forward.

577
00:46:57.860 --> 00:47:00.820
Leave him! Leave him where he fell.

578
00:48:12.600 --> 00:48:13.930
Where is he?

579
00:48:14.020 --> 00:48:15.890
Aemond One-Eye. We know he's been here.

580
00:48:16.940 --> 00:48:19.060
Good ser. this has become tiresome.

581
00:48:20.230 --> 00:48:22.650
I'm of a mind to send a message
to the queen myself.

582
00:48:22.730 --> 00:48:24.190
He's not here.

583
00:48:24.280 --> 00:48:26.400
-He has never been here.
-She's lying.

584
00:48:26.490 --> 00:48:28.700
I've heard about you. witch.

585
00:48:28.780 --> 00:48:31.370
She's no witch. She's an imbecile.

586
00:48:32.120 --> 00:48:34.870
Cast out and wandering.
Touched in the head.

587
00:48:34.950 --> 00:48:36.620
Though not in the cunny
for too long. I think.

588
00:48:36.710 --> 00:48:39.830
Will you speak to me thus
in the very shadow of my fortress?

589
00:48:39.920 --> 00:48:41.710
It's been weeks since I've had a woman.

590
00:48:41.790 --> 00:48:44.260
I'm going to fuck you
and make you my salt wife.

591
00:48:58.810 --> 00:48:59.850
Ah!

592
00:49:24.710 --> 00:49:26.760
Seems you've taken a turn for the better.

593
00:49:36.890 --> 00:49:40.100
In Essos. we can secrete His Grace
until the time is right for his return.

594
00:49:40.190 --> 00:49:43.230
But we are watched now.
We can linger here no longer.

595
00:49:43.310 --> 00:49:45.610
-You risk his safety merely by speaking--
-An ocean passage beset

596
00:49:45.690 --> 00:49:48.990
by pirates. and dragons.
and storms. and then what?

597
00:49:49.070 --> 00:49:51.320
Eating dates and incense while Westeros

598
00:49:51.410 --> 00:49:53.870
-is reduced to ash?
-His Grace is in no state to fight.

599
00:49:53.950 --> 00:49:55.700
Neither would he tolerate
the Braavosi heat.

600
00:49:56.790 --> 00:49:59.000
-The monkeys alone--
-You surprise me. Lannister.

601
00:49:59.080 --> 00:50:00.620
Such a distaste for the foreign.

602
00:50:00.710 --> 00:50:03.960
I have lived with these people.
Do you forget? I've eaten with them.

603
00:50:04.040 --> 00:50:06.380
fought with them. shared everything
with them. even their...

604
00:50:08.090 --> 00:50:09.300
Yes?

605
00:50:10.300 --> 00:50:11.510
I know what they are.

606
00:50:13.510 --> 00:50:15.680
In Braavos.
I have prepared the means for us

607
00:50:15.760 --> 00:50:17.930
to live in a manner as befits His Grace.

608
00:50:18.020 --> 00:50:19.730
-We can ascertain--
-He is the king. Larys.

609
00:50:19.810 --> 00:50:22.730
Not some chip for you to hold
until such time as benefits you.

610
00:50:22.810 --> 00:50:25.150
-I have men riding with me--
-Sellswords.

611
00:50:25.230 --> 00:50:26.650
Cheaply bought. by the look of them.

612
00:50:26.730 --> 00:50:30.320
We need only bring him to Lannisport.
where he will be sheltered.

613
00:50:30.400 --> 00:50:32.740
From there. we may summon and command
what strength remains to us.

614
00:50:32.820 --> 00:50:34.450
Yes. no doubt it would be
the making of the Lannisters

615
00:50:34.530 --> 00:50:36.740
to declare Casterly Rock
the new seat of the king.

616
00:50:36.830 --> 00:50:38.290
Do you think even now
of your own advancement?

617
00:50:38.370 --> 00:50:41.290
Oh. begging your pardon.
most selfless of servants.

618
00:50:41.370 --> 00:50:43.170
I was only risking my life
at sea for our common cause.

619
00:50:43.250 --> 00:50:44.880
Gregor. is it?

620
00:50:44.960 --> 00:50:47.170
It seems I missed the salient moment
when His Grace made you Hand.

621
00:50:53.050 --> 00:50:56.140
You may call me "Your Grace."

622
00:51:08.650 --> 00:51:11.990
There is an evil spirit afoot.
This is no man. I tell you.

623
00:51:12.070 --> 00:51:14.700
Do not shame yourself. Ned.
We're knights. not infants.

624
00:51:14.780 --> 00:51:18.950
But we will find these cravens
and make a grim example of them.

625
00:51:19.030 --> 00:51:21.870
We are hunters. Not prey.

626
00:51:21.950 --> 00:51:24.920
-Hunters get paid.
-It's not safe out there!

627
00:51:27.420 --> 00:51:28.670
Enough.

628
00:51:30.000 --> 00:51:31.710
You and I are the protectors and keepers

629
00:51:31.800 --> 00:51:34.170
of the greatest Citadel
in all of Westeros.

630
00:51:35.680 --> 00:51:37.640
The governing seat of a mighty realm.

631
00:51:40.930 --> 00:51:44.100
Without the City Watch. without us...

632
00:51:46.480 --> 00:51:48.650
these streets would echo
with the cries of insurrection.

633
00:51:51.030 --> 00:51:54.400
The alleys of King's Landing would boil
with corruption and depravity.

634
00:51:54.490 --> 00:51:58.870
I look to you now to uphold your vows
to the city and to the throne.

635
00:51:58.950 --> 00:52:03.450
Trust in your queen. and I pledge you.
you will be repaid twice over

636
00:52:03.540 --> 00:52:05.580
for the sacrifices you make now.

637
00:52:08.290 --> 00:52:11.840
And in the years to come.
as Dorne finally bends the knee...

638
00:52:14.050 --> 00:52:15.670
...as Rhaenyra's great empire grows

639
00:52:15.760 --> 00:52:18.090
and the Seven Kingdoms become Nine.

640
00:52:18.180 --> 00:52:21.470
become Twelve. become the new Valyria.

641
00:52:22.640 --> 00:52:26.140
When I return with wagons
spilling over with silks and silver.

642
00:52:26.230 --> 00:52:28.150
who will be the first...

643
00:52:29.480 --> 00:52:31.900
...to celebrate in the spoils of conquest?

644
00:52:31.980 --> 00:52:33.230
We will!

645
00:52:34.360 --> 00:52:35.860
Groups of three and four!

646
00:52:35.940 --> 00:52:37.990
No man walks alone.

647
00:52:38.070 --> 00:52:41.490
Woodgard. Owtram.
you oversee the market square.

648
00:52:44.410 --> 00:52:47.580
It seems the Lord of Flea Bottom
has not been altogether forgotten.

649
00:52:47.670 --> 00:52:49.790
We've apprehended someone. Your Grace.

650
00:52:49.880 --> 00:52:51.210
At River Row.

651
00:52:51.840 --> 00:52:53.800
Then he will be the first to be repaid.

652
00:52:56.010 --> 00:52:57.720
Fall in!

653
00:52:57.800 --> 00:52:59.760
Stoney Sept beyond the rise!

654
00:53:21.870 --> 00:53:23.280
What is it?

655
00:53:26.500 --> 00:53:28.120
The Rivermen have crossed.

656
00:53:29.620 --> 00:53:31.250
And burned the bridge behind them.

657
00:53:33.130 --> 00:53:35.710
We can no longer delay their march.

658
00:53:40.880 --> 00:53:42.220
So we failed.

659
00:54:17.960 --> 00:54:19.260
How many others?

660
00:54:19.340 --> 00:54:21.010
Who was with you?

661
00:54:24.800 --> 00:54:27.140
I was the only one. I swear it.

662
00:54:28.180 --> 00:54:31.100
-I acted alone.
-Under whose instruction?

663
00:54:31.190 --> 00:54:33.440
I never saw his face. I told you.

664
00:54:33.520 --> 00:54:34.980
The tongue or the eye?

665
00:54:38.940 --> 00:54:39.860
The eye.

666
00:54:41.360 --> 00:54:44.240
It was the king. he said! Please!

667
00:54:46.200 --> 00:54:48.450
He said it was the king's work
I was to be about.

668
00:54:48.540 --> 00:54:49.870
It was Aegon then.

669
00:54:51.870 --> 00:54:53.080
No.

670
00:54:54.830 --> 00:54:56.380
Look.

671
00:54:58.670 --> 00:55:00.170
In my boot.

672
00:55:05.090 --> 00:55:07.970
Compliments of
King Daeron Targaryen. he said.

673
00:55:09.100 --> 00:55:11.890
For killing traitors to his throne.

674
00:55:20.440 --> 00:55:21.490
No!

675
00:55:21.570 --> 00:55:23.530
No! No! Please!

676
00:55:28.530 --> 00:55:30.410
There's none who
may say that you did not give

677
00:55:30.490 --> 00:55:32.120
your best effort.

678
00:55:32.200 --> 00:55:36.080
Perhaps this is the best
we could have hoped for.

679
00:55:37.080 --> 00:55:41.130
We've made our mark and returned alive...

680
00:55:42.920 --> 00:55:44.420
...to Tumbleton. perhaps...

681
00:55:45.930 --> 00:55:47.930
to find out what Ormund has planned.

682
00:55:50.560 --> 00:55:52.720
I thank you for your offer. Ser Gwayne.

683
00:55:54.980 --> 00:55:56.650
But my path is set before me.

684
00:55:58.650 --> 00:56:00.520
And what is...

685
00:56:00.610 --> 00:56:01.980
What is that path?

686
00:56:03.570 --> 00:56:05.200
We'll raft the river.

687
00:56:06.200 --> 00:56:07.660
Or swim it.

688
00:56:09.280 --> 00:56:11.660
It was one thing to obstruct them.
Ser Criston. but...

689
00:56:13.370 --> 00:56:15.660
you must see they've gained the advantage.

690
00:56:17.250 --> 00:56:18.500
What more can we do?

691
00:56:18.580 --> 00:56:20.250
We will join them...

692
00:56:21.340 --> 00:56:22.750
in battle.

693
00:56:23.760 --> 00:56:25.760
Face them head on.

694
00:56:25.840 --> 00:56:27.930
We have half the men that we set out with.

695
00:56:29.470 --> 00:56:31.720
There are 200 Rivermen
for every one of us.

696
00:56:32.760 --> 00:56:34.520
That-- you...

697
00:56:35.270 --> 00:56:37.190
It would march us towards certain death.

698
00:56:52.160 --> 00:56:55.200
This was your goal. wasn't it?

699
00:56:56.580 --> 00:56:57.790
All along.

700
00:56:58.620 --> 00:57:00.790
Our fate was always assured. Ser Gwayne.

701
00:57:03.170 --> 00:57:05.090
When we set out. we were doomed...

702
00:57:06.050 --> 00:57:08.010
to death and defeat.

703
00:57:08.090 --> 00:57:10.680
I have offered you sanctuary.

704
00:57:11.850 --> 00:57:13.310
Or at least the hope of one.

705
00:57:13.390 --> 00:57:15.350
You have offered me service to your house.

706
00:57:17.940 --> 00:57:19.560
I am grateful.

707
00:57:22.360 --> 00:57:24.730
But I have been a servant all my life.

708
00:57:27.400 --> 00:57:28.990
To green or to black.

709
00:57:31.200 --> 00:57:33.490
I have defined myself by oaths...

710
00:57:34.910 --> 00:57:36.410
through unyielding devotion.

711
00:57:37.960 --> 00:57:41.000
And the highborn have made much of me
while it pleased them to do so.

712
00:57:45.210 --> 00:57:47.300
But I will not let them diminish me now.

713
00:57:50.550 --> 00:57:53.720
I will not return spurned...

714
00:57:55.350 --> 00:57:56.720
rejected.

715
00:57:59.350 --> 00:58:01.440
I am the realm's greatest warrior.

716
00:58:04.020 --> 00:58:05.690
And I will die as such.

717
00:58:08.030 --> 00:58:09.190
Clear-eyed.

718
00:58:10.610 --> 00:58:11.700
Unbent.

719
00:58:13.490 --> 00:58:14.910
Glorious in battle.

720
00:58:17.160 --> 00:58:20.120
And not in their service. finally.

721
00:58:22.170 --> 00:58:23.380
But in my own.

722
00:58:28.090 --> 00:58:29.880
And they will sing songs of it.

723
00:58:36.010 --> 00:58:38.060
And Queen Alicent herself will hear them.

724
00:58:46.610 --> 00:58:49.570
The plan is to rebuild
the fleet at Driftmark.

725
00:58:49.650 --> 00:58:51.570
but it will take time.

726
00:58:51.650 --> 00:58:53.450
The Velaryon resources are diminished.

727
00:58:54.570 --> 00:58:57.120
A condition with which
I am all too familiar.

728
00:58:57.200 --> 00:58:58.830
The king consort. Your Grace.

729
00:59:00.500 --> 00:59:02.000
My prince.

730
00:59:04.790 --> 00:59:06.750
The price of our humiliation.

731
00:59:10.010 --> 00:59:11.970
-What is this?
-Who is this.

732
00:59:13.380 --> 00:59:15.550
Young Daeron Targaryen.

733
00:59:15.640 --> 00:59:17.800
Ormund has declared him king.

734
00:59:20.270 --> 00:59:22.140
We should have burned them
when we had the chance.

735
00:59:32.400 --> 00:59:34.450
We have endured much.

736
00:59:34.530 --> 00:59:36.660
Suffered much.

737
00:59:37.620 --> 00:59:39.240
This I know.

738
00:59:41.580 --> 00:59:44.370
And though we languish now...

739
00:59:45.500 --> 00:59:46.750
in the darkness...

740
00:59:48.790 --> 00:59:50.710
we will not lose heart.

741
00:59:52.300 --> 00:59:53.970
Come to bed.

742
00:59:55.550 --> 00:59:56.930
She hears something.

743
01:00:02.890 --> 01:00:05.060
The Seven watch over us even now.

744
01:00:11.690 --> 01:00:13.150
Look.

745
01:00:19.700 --> 01:00:21.410
Let the Maiden grant us vision.

746
01:00:22.790 --> 01:00:24.620
For the way ahead is blessed.

747
01:00:32.670 --> 01:00:35.130
Let the Warrior lend us his sword

748
01:00:38.590 --> 01:00:40.600
that we do not falter in our resolve.

749
01:00:42.310 --> 01:00:43.890
And the Smith...

750
01:00:46.730 --> 01:00:48.060
Let's go.

751
01:00:49.600 --> 01:00:52.150
Let the Smith bless us with his strength.

752
01:00:54.820 --> 01:00:56.900
The Crone lights our way.

753
01:00:59.280 --> 01:01:01.740
Ours is the path of righteousness.

754
01:01:05.870 --> 01:01:06.960
Ser Luthor?

755
01:01:13.130 --> 01:01:14.630
Careful.

756
01:01:14.710 --> 01:01:16.510
The Mother gives her comfort.

757
01:01:17.670 --> 01:01:19.380
The Father. his protection.

758
01:01:20.800 --> 01:01:23.350
No. No. it's blocked.

759
01:01:24.470 --> 01:01:25.600
We have to go back.

760
01:01:25.680 --> 01:01:28.020
There is no way back. the door is shut!

761
01:01:35.070 --> 01:01:37.190
No. no. no. no. no! No!

762
01:01:40.160 --> 01:01:41.700
And the Stranger...

763
01:02:02.220 --> 01:02:04.390
The Stranger offers us rest.

